## Obsidian WIKI — team vault (use it fully)

**SQLite (`mimir.db`) is canonical.** The **Obsidian vault** is the **WIKI mirror**: graph view, backlinks, reading, and search — not a second database.

### Stable vault path (your usual setup)

- Configure **one vault** the team always uses (e.g. **`N:/WIKI/atlas_wiki/vault`**): **`obsidian.vault_path`** in **`<MIMIR_repo>/.mimir/config.yaml`**, or **`MIMIR_OBSIDIAN_VAULT_PATH`** on the Mimir MCP server in Cursor. Prefer **forward slashes** on Windows in YAML.
- After changing **vault path**, **Obsidian env vars**, or **`.mimir/config.yaml`**, **restart the Mimir MCP server** (Cursor: **Developer: Reload Window**, or disable/enable the Mimir MCP entry) so the process reloads config. Confirm stderr: **`[mimir-mcp] version:`** and **`[mimir-mcp] obsidian wiki: <vault> → KGRAPH/...`**.

### Per project (new repo or existing — correct WIKI shape)

Under that vault, Mimir writes:

| Location | Role |
|----------|------|
| **`01_PROJECTS/<slug>.md`** | Registry note: **`mimir_project_name`** (frontmatter) + **verbatim README** of the product + “Knowledge graph” section linking into **`KGRAPH/<slug>/`**. |
| **`KGRAPH/<slug>/`** | Mirrored ledger: **`MOC.md`**, **`Episodes/`**, **`Tasks/`**, **`Intents/`**, **`Validations/`**, **`Subsystems/`**, **`Traces/`**. |

**`<slug>` must match the codebase you are mirroring**, not a generic default when you are **not** developing the Mimir repo itself:

- Set **`obsidian.project_slug`** (or **`MIMIR_OBSIDIAN_PROJECT_SLUG`**) to a stable id for the **opened workspace** (e.g. repo or product name, filesystem-safe).
- Set **`obsidian.project_name`** / **`MIMIR_OBSIDIAN_PROJECT_NAME`** for a readable Obsidian title.
- Set **`obsidian.readme_path`** or **`MIMIR_OBSIDIAN_README_PATH`** to the **absolute path** of that workspace’s **`README.md`** so **`01_PROJECTS/<slug>.md`** documents the **right product**. If you omit this while working outside the Mimir repo, the note may embed **Mimir’s** README by mistake — **fix path when switching projects**.

### What agents should do

1. **Normal workflow unchanged** — record decisions, validations, episodes, subsystems, traces; when the vault resolves, live sync updates **`KGRAPH/<slug>/`**.
2. **After bulk SQLite changes** that do not re-trigger per-row sync — run **`mimir_obsidian_backfill`** (especially after **`mimir_team_ledger_import`** or **`mimir_run_gc`**).
3. **When helping the user in Obsidian** — point to **`01_PROJECTS/<slug>.md`** (overview + README) and **`KGRAPH/<slug>/MOC.md`** (map of mirrored memory). Wikilinks use vault-relative paths.
4. **If the user opens a different repo** in Cursor but keeps the same vault — remind them to update **slug / name / readme_path** (or MCP env) so notes do not overwrite the wrong **`KGRAPH/<slug>/`** tree.

### MCP server update (after pulling Mimir)

On the machine that runs MCP: **`git pull`** in the Mimir repo (e.g. **`N:\MIMIR`**), then **`npm ci`** (or **`npm install`** when the lockfile did not change). **Restart** the Mimir MCP server in Cursor. On stderr, confirm **`[mimir-mcp] version:`** matches **`package.json`** in that repo.

